questiontext.text:
For this exercise, you need to compute the cross-sectional area of a pipe.  The input to the program will be two radius values (expressed in cm): the first input is the larger radius (r1) from the center to the outer edge of the pipe, and the second input is the smaller radius (r2) from the center to the inner edge of the pipe.


Your program should compute the cross-sectional area (i.e. the blue portion in the figure above).  The output should include the units "cm^2". 

NOTES:

  • Your program should use the following fixed value for PI: 3.14159
  • The correct conversion specifier for reading doubles is: %lf
  • The output should be expressed to 3 decimal places
